{
  "text": "L f is relatively large because the switching speed of stateof-the-art power switches, at ultrahigh voltage and power transfer levels, is not expected to exceed 1 kHz [CITATION_1] , and similar problem can be found in the sine-wave modulated MDCCs [CITATION_2] - [CITATION_3] . However, such large inductor design is technically feasible and widely applied in the constructed line commutation converter (LCC) [CITATION_4] and MMC based HVDC projects [CITATION_5] , and the coupled inductors can be employed to cancel the dc flux and reduce the total core volume (coupled inductors can be installed in bipolar converter or unipolar converter with even phase legs [CITATION_6] ). For instance, thanks to the mutual inductance, L f can be reduced to about 110mH if the coefficient of mutual induction is 0.8.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "28438523",
    "[CITATION_2]": "40281803",
    "[CITATION_3]": "34490438",
